[1] Palestinian authority: genotyping
Date: Tue 7 Jan 2014 [accessed]
Source: Global FMD Situation, European Commission for the Control of FMD (EUFMD) [summ., edited]
http://www.fao.org/fileadmin/user_upload/eufmd/docs/FMD_monthly_reports/November_2013_FMD_global_report.pdf


Foot-and-mouth disease situation, FAO monthly report, November 2013
POOL 3 -- West Eurasia & Middle East: Palestine
-------------------------------------------------------------------
In Jericho, West Bank an outbreak of FMD serotype O virus was detected in a flock of 200 sheep, with about 30 percent morbidity (diagnosis confirmed by the FMD laboratory at the Kimron Veterinary Institute).

The virus belongs to topotypes ME-SA, genotype/strain PanAsia-2FAR-09 and is 98.59 percent identical at VP1 with viruses detected in Turkey in 2013. This 1.41 percent VP1 difference suggests considerable virus circulation has occurred between the outbreaks detected in Turkey and that in Palestine. This highlights the need for more surveillance in countries in the neighbourhood of Turkey, Israel, and Palestine to determine the FMD situation more accurately.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The WRLFMD genotyping report of 2 samples from sheep in Jericho, Palestinian Autonomous Territories, collected 21 Nov 2013, is available, with compared other regional strains and reference (vaccine) strains at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/2013/WRLFMD-2013-00029%20O%20Palestinian%20AT%202013.pdf. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Palestinian Authority is available at http://healthmap.org/r/2c2O. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

